structured.title: Rachel and Partner Plan Upcoming Sundays At Church
structured.overview: Rachel and her partner discuss scheduling responsibilities for two upcoming Sundays at their church. Rachel insists that one of those Sundays must be a breakfast church service because she cannot cover two consecutive weeks of kids’ church due to a lack of leaders. The user has already offered preaching dates to Johnny and Steve, including a standalone sermon topic about being servant-hearted and another on "what do we believe by faith," and is reluctant to overuse Johnny or push Steve’s next preaching slot too far back (possibly to May). They consider designating the flexible-topic Sunday as breakfast church so Rachel and her partner might briefly attend before traveling, and Rachel notes they must confirm details with Lois and Rana, who organize things. They also consider using the first Sunday as a calm family morning before heading off, even if the boys don’t attend church that day.

apps_results.content:
## Scheduling Two Sundays  
- Need one Sunday as breakfast church  
- Cannot cover kids' church two weeks running  
- No children’s work possible one of those weeks  

## Preaching Assignments  
- Johnny given one standalone “servant-hearted” sermon  
- Steve offered the other Sunday and more dates  
- Concern Steve’s next preach may slip to May  

## Content of Sermons  
- Johnny’s “servant-hearted” talk expected low quality  
- Steve also assigned “What do we believe by faith?”  
- Any-topic slot to be during breakfast church  

## Coordination and Attendance  
- Must confirm Steve’s actual preaching date  
- Need to check dates with Lois and Rana  
- Family likely away for two Sundays in March  

## Next Steps  
- Adjust which Sunday is breakfast church  
- Confirm Steve’s preaching schedule and communicate changes  
- Inform Lois and Rana about absences and logistics
